ut Elasticsearch requires HTTPS. The real issue might be that the elastic password was already rotated in Elasticsearch itself, so the auth-checker is failing because it's still using the old password from the `elastic-password` secret—I need to update that secret with the new password value. is that Elasticsearch requires HTTPS on port 9200 based on the security configuration, so the auth-checker's HTTP connection would fail. I should verify this by testing from within the cluster to confirm whether both protocols are available or if HTTPS is the only option.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1017,"cache_read_input_tokens":33133,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1017},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fc7714d-38fd-4a9a-8ccb-1e4fbf935d9b","uuid":"cf0c6b73-b90b-4708-88d9-2775210746e3","request_id":"req_011CceqzkujDKpifh4A321mk"}
